{"TopicId":130599,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Possibility of a space elevator on Gilly?","CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T03:58:41Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T03:58:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just realized that the length of a possible space elevator on Gilly can be\u00A0completely within the render distance. 42.14 km length vs 45 km diameter (of render distance sphere). Is this feasible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T04:00:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would probably take up the entirety of Gilly. \u00A0It might have low gravity, but that\u0027s because it\u0027s small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"justspace103","CreatedById":64088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T04:30:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits possible, but you wouldnt need it because gilly is so small\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Temstar","CreatedById":24430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T04:52:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376657\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453607921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n42.14 km length\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has to be longer than that, 42.14km is only the half way station, you need more elevator above this point so that the whole elevator will be taut and in tension. It doesn\u0027t necessarily have to be much longer though, if you tether something heavy like say an E class asteroid on the far end then the upper section of the elevator can probably be pretty short.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordKael","CreatedById":154046,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T05:18:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, you can basically jump off gilly and be on an escape trajectory, so whats the point?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T05:59:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453612716\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154046\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordKael\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, LordKael said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, you can basically jump off gilly and be on an escape trajectory, so whats the point?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you had this situation IRL, you could use the elevator as a big maglev accelerator. Load up some ore into the elevator and activate it, it\u0027ll shoot right back to Earth/Kerbin if you time it right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-24T06:00:24Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2016 06:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Findthepin1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rocketbuilder","CreatedById":154102,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T11:08:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust jump!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453612716\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154046\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LordKael\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, LordKael said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, you can basically jump off gilly and be on an escape trajectory, so whats the point?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T15:08:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA space ladder would be sufficient for Gilly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jetski","CreatedById":119969,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T15:28:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild it! \u00A0Get the bigger vab mod and hyperedit to start. Biggest I\u0027ve ever assembled was 1km in LKO, just girders and SAS really. Maybe tweakscale too? \u00A0Epic if you can tether the top to an asteroid without kraken eating you\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tatonf","CreatedById":146283,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T16:53:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIRL something like a balista would probably be more efficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Optimist","CreatedById":151904,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T17:35:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222377205\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453654383\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146283\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tatonf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, Tatonf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIRL something like a balista would probably be more efficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tatonf","CreatedById":146283,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T17:41:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.noelshack.com/2016-03-1453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-catapult.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://image.noelshack.com/minis/2016/03/1453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-catapult.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u00221453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-cata\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Optimist","CreatedById":151904,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T18:34:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222377282\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453657309\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146283\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tatonf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Tatonf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.noelshack.com/2016-03-1453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-catapult.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00221453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-cata\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://image.noelshack.com/minis/2016/03/1453657293-greek-and-roman-ballista-catapult.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoesn\u0027t look very space-age to me\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tatonf","CreatedById":146283,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T19:13:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, it\u0027s a siege engine used in the classical antiquity and middle ages. But old doesn\u0027t mean useless. You could still build something very similar that would launch things in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you could use a catapulta.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T21:32:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376657\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453607921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just realized that the length of a possible space elevator on Gilly can be\u00A0completely within the render distance. 42.14 km length vs 45 km diameter (of render distance sphere). Is this feasible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe physics bubble is much smaller, about 2.5km in vacuum and 22ish km in atmosphere. Sorry, the space elevator won\u0027t fit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lukethecoder64","CreatedById":148786,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T21:38:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222377591\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453671169\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe physics bubble is much smaller, about 2.5km in vacuum and 22ish km in atmosphere. Sorry, the space elevator won\u0027t fit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats not how it works. The currently loaded vessel can be as big as your RAM will allow:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gI22NS4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gI22NS4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d have problems climbing up it, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-24T21:43:07Z\u0022 title=\u002201/24/2016 09:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by lukethecoder64\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-24T21:42:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222377610\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453671537\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148786\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lukethecoder64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, lukethecoder64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats not how it works. The currently loaded vessel can be as big as your ram will allow:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gI22NS4.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gI22NS4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gI22NS4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d have problems climbing up it, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPictured craft is \u0026lt;22.5km long, so....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"problemecium","CreatedById":101649,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T03:03:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. And if by \u0022render distance\u0022 you mean the distance at which craft will load, we\u0027re looking at a radius of 2.25 km (or up to 2.5) and thus a diameter of 4.5 km (or up to 5), not 45. Unless I misunderstand, you seem to have shifted a decimal point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Halo_003","CreatedById":76050,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T04:19:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy would you need a space elevator on Gilly? You can almost jump into orbit.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T05:41:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378008\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453691020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022101649\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022parameciumkid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, parameciumkid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. And if by \u0022render distance\u0022 you mean the distance at which craft will load, we\u0027re looking at a radius of 2.25 km (or up to 2.5) and thus a diameter of 4.5 km (or up to 5), not 45. Unless I misunderstand, you seem to have shifted a decimal point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe physics bubble is larger in atmo than in vacuum now, it\u0027s 2.5ish km in vacuum and 22.5ish km in atmo, a change made to make recovery more feasible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Champ","CreatedById":96425,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T08:39:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222376741\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453615166\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 24/1/2016 at 6:59 AM, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if you had this situation IRL, you could use the elevator as a big maglev accelerator. Load up some ore into the elevator and activate it, it\u0027ll shoot right back to Earth/Kerbin if you time it right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you are wrong : a space elevator gets you to geostationnary orbit, not escape velocity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RizzoTheRat","CreatedById":123362,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T09:11:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378097\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453695592\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276050\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Halo_003\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Halo_003 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy would you need a space elevator on Gilly? You can almost jump into orbit.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause SPACE ELEVATOR!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453711189\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296425\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Champ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, Champ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you are wrong : a space elevator gets you to geostationnary orbit, not escape velocity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt goes through geostationary, but unless it\u0027s rigidly supporting it\u0027s own weight you\u0027d extend it beyond geostationary so it\u0027s in tension (hence the comments about attaching an asteroid, this would be beyond geostationary otherwise the weight of the tether would deorbit it).\u00A0 Plus even on a tower than only extended to geostationary, there\u0027s no reason whatever you send up it needs to be sent slowly, most of the trip up is in near vacuum so you could accelerate a payload to a pretty high radial speed by the time it hits the top.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Champ","CreatedById":96425,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T12:06:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378263\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453713066\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123362\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RizzoTheRat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RizzoTheRat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause SPACE ELEVATOR!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt goes through geostationary, but unless it\u0027s rigidly supporting it\u0027s own weight you\u0027d extend it beyond geostationary so it\u0027s in tension (hence the comments about attaching an asteroid, this would be beyond geostationary otherwise the weight of the tether would deorbit it).\u00A0 Plus even on a tower than only extended to geostationary, there\u0027s no reason whatever you send up it needs to be sent slowly, most of the trip up is in near vacuum so you could accelerate a payload to a pretty high radial speed by the time it hits the top.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, you are right, and i was wrong : i thought the attached asteroid needed to be in geostationary orbit or else the counterweight would move faster/slower than the surface, and that would destroy the elevator, but i was wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"problemecium","CreatedById":101649,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-25T23:34:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222378150\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221453700513\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe physics bubble is larger in atmo than in vacuum now, it\u0027s 2.5ish km in vacuum and 22.5ish km in atmo, a change made to make recovery more feasible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yeah. I\u0027d forgotten about that.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot that it matters on Gilly where there\u0027s no atmosphere, heh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monophonic","CreatedById":76902,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-26T11:53:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow you guys got me wondering, whether the physic limit is truly such that any parts falling outside the bubble will not simulate physics, or if it simply looks at the CoM of the vessel in question, then simulates the vessel in it\u0027s entirety if the CoM is in range. (Or the root part even.)\u00A0The latter would be a\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Elot\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0simpler to program for nearly the same result \u002B avoid any kraken attacks from having physics calculated for only some parts of a ship. If it is the latter, you could build the space elevator but it would only work as long as you stayed close to the CoM (or root part, whichever it used.) So not very useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}